        {
            "title": "德國投資者預期指數意外下滑 經濟復甦信心受挫",
            "description": "<div class=\"atoms\"><figure class=\"mb-module-gap\"><div class=\"mx-auto w-fit\"><img alt=\"ZEW\" class=\"rounded-lg\" height=\"562\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/YlLq1kbi84HIjCEEb0mV8A--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTk2MDtoPTU2Mg--/https://media.zenfs.com/no/bloomberg_chinese_traditional_757/f6bf84aa3431893bab0423722bc67d08\" width=\"960\"/><figcaption class=\"text-px14 text-dolphin mt-2 wrap-anywhere\" style=\"max-width:960px\">ZEW</figcaption></div></figure><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\"><br/></p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\"><span class=\"news-dateline\">【彭博】--</span> 德國2月份投資者信心意外下滑，令這個歐洲最大經濟體即將迎來強勁復甦的預期有所降溫。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">ZEW institute的一項預期指數從1月的59.6降至58.3。此前彭博調查的分析師預期該指數將躍升至65.2。當前狀況指數則如預期有所改善。</p><figure class=\"mb-module-gap\"><div class=\"mx-auto w-fit\"><img alt=\" \" class=\"rounded-lg\" height=\"562\" src=\"https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/U79zUYVXCnlfc8hwZuwlqg--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTk2MDtoPTU2Mg--/https://media.zenfs.com/no/bloomberg_chinese_traditional_757/dc6e12230ba59f5febdcdd859d274fa7\" width=\"960\"/><figcaption class=\"text-px14 text-dolphin mt-2 wrap-anywhere\" style=\"max-width:960px\"> </figcaption></div></figure><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">ZEW總裁Achim Wambach表示，儘管經濟已進入「復甦階段」，但復甦態勢仍顯脆弱。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">他周二在聲明中指出，「尤其在工業和私人投資領域，仍存在諸多結構性挑戰。亟待推進的社會保險體系改革應成為顯著提升德國作為商業地點吸引力的重要契機。」</p><div class=\"bg-toast-background -mx-5 -mt-2 mb-3 pb-3 md:-mx-0 lg:mx-auto lg:w-[300px] lg:pb-0\"><div class=\"text-px14 text-gandalf py-1 text-center leading-5\">廣告</div><div class=\"mx-auto text-center min-w-[300px] min-h-[250px]\" id=\"sda-inbody-4bdd5611-d3cd-3cf4-8792-b801c5f7c93b-1-iframe\"><div class=\"bg-dirty-seagull text-px12 text-dolphin mx-auto hidden items-center justify-center only:flex w-[300px] h-[250px]\">廣告</div></div></div><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">數千億歐元的基建與國防支出有望推動經濟顯著復甦，去年德國經濟勉強實現成長，這是自2022年以來首次年度成長。德國總理弗里德里希·默茨將0.2%的增速稱為「不儘人意」。</p><div class=\"recommendation-contents\"><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mb-2 h-[30px] w-[80px] rounded-lg\"></div><div class=\"no-scrollbar -mx-5 mb-5 flex overflow-hidden overflow-x-auto md:-mx-2 lg:mb-3.5\"><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mr-2 ml-5 h-[92px] w-[calc(85%-28px)] flex-shrink-0 rounded-lg md:ml-2 md:w-[calc(85%-16px)] lg:h-[120px] lg:w-[calc(50%-16px)]\"></div><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mx-2 h-[92px] w-[85%] flex-shrink-0 rounded-lg lg:h-[120px] lg:w-[calc(50%-16px)]\"></div></div></div><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">政府預測今年國內生產毛額將成長1%。德國央行及部分分析師則更為樂觀，德意志銀行預計增速將達1.5%。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">但潛在風險依然存在，包括美國總統唐納德·川普貿易政策的突發變動以及來自中國的競爭。官僚主義和競爭力不足等長期存在的結構性問題也亟待解決。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">原文標題German Investor Outlook Unexpectedly Sours in Blow to Recovery</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">--聯合報導 Iain Rogers、Joel Rinneby、Harumi Ichikura、Mark Evans.</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">More stories like this are available on <a class=\"link\" data-ylk=\"slk:bloomberg.com;elm:context_link;itc:0;sec:content-canvas\" href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">bloomberg.com</a></p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">©2026 Bloomberg L.P.</p></div>",
